children.name: ROUGE metric
children.description: ROUGE, or Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation, is a set of metrics and a software package used for evaluating automatic summarization and machine translation in natural language processing. The metrics compare the overlap of tokens or N-grams of an automatically produced summary or translation against a reference or a set of references (human-produced) summary or translation. (Sources: Wikipedia, BioASQ).
